headlines.description: — Trae Young had 40 points and 13 assists, Dejounte Murray added 32 points and the Atlanta Hawks overcame a slow start and spotty late foul shooting to beat the Washington Wizards 130-126 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trae Young has 40 points and 13 assists, Hawks outlast Wizards 130-126

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson has no interest in forgetting the New Orleans Pelicans' most embarrassing loss of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zion Williamson, Brandon Ingram each score 26 points, Pelicans top Lakers 129-109

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander had 24 points and six assists and the Oklahoma City Thunder won their fourth straight game, beating the Brooklyn Nets 124-108 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 24, Thunder beat Nets 124-108, extend winning streak to 4 games

events.name: Boston Celtics at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 25 points, Jaylen Brown added 24 and the Boston Celtics extended their winning streak to six games with a 134-101 win over the San Antonio Spurs on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics extend winning streak to 6 games with a 134-101 rout of the Spurs

headlines.description: — Malik Monk scored 27 points, Domantas Sabonis added 13 points, 21 rebounds and 12 assists and the Sacramento Kings routed the Memphis Grizzlies 123-92 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Malik Monk, Domantas Sabonis lead the Kings to a 123-92 victory over the Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal took off on the break, received the pass in stride from Devin Booker and threw down a powerful two-handed jam over Orlando's Jalen Suggs in the third quarter.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant scores 31 points, Beal adds season-high 25 to help Suns beat Magic 112-107
